reviewText: This is for my grandaughter, she wanted the complete season 5.

Had to get this to add to my collection. This is one of the best MTV shows ever put on. I just knew I had to get it when i saw that it was pre order. You won't go wrong. The only thing i didn't like was that they split in 2  parts. but I can't wait to watch it again. so pick it up you won't be sorry.

Just as an FYI for anyone interested...Colton Haynes is not in season  of Teen Wolf...he hasn't been a part of the cast since season 2...he is reported to possible come back next season but no guarantee...Tyler Posey is and always will be the star of this show...

The item description needs to be updated to reflect the fact that actor Colton Haynes doesn't star in season 5. In fact, he hasn't been on the show since season 2. Apart from this mistake, the fifth season has been fairly good.

It is my favorite show! Since I came across it in Amazon video app, I've watched every episode in 1 week! It is THAT great! This series is by far the best story of supernatural werewolves and creatures I've ever watched/read/ or heard! It is dark but light, and I've loved learning about the characters as they learn their powers (although Lydia's took awhile). Stiles and Scott are by far my favorites, but the rest of the cast are so phenomenal too! MTV rocks with this show!

I highly recommend if you're a first time viewer to buy all of the seasons and watch them to get the full understanding and excitement that the show brings.

We have enjoyed this series "overall" but the writers are apparently homosexual or have an affinity for homosexuals. Season three, was almost as bad and then it got a little better, but season five is full of gay story lines. I think gays people have every right to be in this country as we do but I am so tired if having them shoved down my throat. They are a very small part of the population and are getting to be a major part of so many characters in TV. It's just Hollywood crap and it won't stop until we stop buying what they are cramming down our throats. We've gotten enough of it and we put season five in the trash after the first disk. I wish homosexuals no harm but I'm tired of seeing it and hearing about it. We're done with this series.
